The paper proposes a novel algorithm for multi-task learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also mentions applications in computer vision and natural language processing, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.CV and cs.CL respectively. The algorithm is based on multiobjective optimization, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions parallel computing, which is often used in neural networks (cs.NE).
